* Prompt source:line information on errors, e.g.:

    exit 123
    echo -n "okay"
    echo -n "okay" > /dev/stderr
    bad stderr (okay, expects okay-), required by 'check-stderr' (from .)
    bad stderr (okay, expects okay-)

  should be:

    exit 123
    echo -n "okay"
    echo -n "okay" > /dev/stderr
    build.smart:15:8: bad stderr (okay, expects okay-), required by 'check-stderr' (from .)
    build.smart:15:8: bad stderr (okay, expects okay-)
